The paper discusses defensive deception in cybersecurity and privacy, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The use of game theory to model defensive deception suggests a focus on strategic decision-making, which is a common theme in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and social networks (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the incentive structures and actions of different types of deception, which could be relevant to the study of cybercrime (cs.CY) and data structures (cs.DS).
